   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Batch Operations — Bulk Ingestion and Export\n",
    "\n",
    "Medha 0.3.0 exposes a full bulk API for populating, exporting, and deduplicating\n",
    "the cache at scale. Use the bulk API when:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Warming the cache** from an existing dataset (CSV, DataFrame, JSON)\n",
    "- **Migrating** between backends or embedders\n",
    "- **Seeding** a staging environment from production data\n",
    "- **Auditing** — exporting all cached queries for analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "| API | When to use |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `store(question, sql)` | Single entry, interactive or low-volume |\n",
    "| `store_many(entries)` | 10–10k entries, in-process list |\n",
    "| `warm_from_dataframe(df)` | Pandas DataFrame, custom column names |\n",
    "| `warm_from_file(path)` | JSON file on disk |\n",
    "| `export_to_dataframe()` | Read all entries into Pandas |\n",
    "| `dedup_collection()` | Remove entries with duplicate SQL |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Requirements:** `pip install \"medha-archai[fastembed]\" pandas tqdm`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import asyncio\n",
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "from medha import Medha, Settings\n",
    "from medha.embeddings.fastembed_adapter import FastEmbedAdapter\n",
    "\n",
    "embedder = FastEmbedAdapter(model_name=\"BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5\", cache_dir=\"./.fastembed_cache\")\n",
    "settings = Settings(backend_type=\"memory\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 1: `store_many()` — Basic Bulk Ingestion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "entries = [\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"How many users are there?\",          \"generated_query\": \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"List all active users\",              \"generated_query\": \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE status = 'active'\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Average salary\",                     \"generated_query\": \"SELECT AVG(salary) FROM employees\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Top 10 products by revenue\",         \"generated_query\": \"SELECT product_id, SUM(amount) FROM orders GROUP BY product_id ORDER BY 2 DESC LIMIT 10\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Orders placed today\",                \"generated_query\": \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders WHERE DATE(created_at) = CURDATE()\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Monthly revenue\",                    \"generated_query\": \"SELECT SUM(amount) FROM orders WHERE MONTH(created_at) = MONTH(NOW())\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Customers with no orders\",           \"generated_query\": \"SELECT * FROM customers WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT customer_id FROM orders)\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Average order value\",                \"generated_query\": \"SELECT AVG(total) FROM orders\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Active sessions count\",              \"generated_query\": \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM sessions WHERE active = true\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Latest 5 registrations\",             \"generated_query\": \"SELECT * FROM users ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 5\"},\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"batch_demo\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    count = await medha.store_many(entries)\n",
    "    print(f\"store_many() stored {count} entries\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    backend_count = await medha._backend.count(\"batch_demo\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Backend count: {backend_count}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 2: Progress Callback — `tqdm` Integration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    from tqdm.auto import tqdm\n",
    "    HAS_TQDM = True\n",
    "except ImportError:\n",
    "    HAS_TQDM = False\n",
    "    print(\"tqdm not installed — showing simple progress\")\n",
    "\n",
    "large_batch = [\n",
    "    {\"question\": f\"Question about metric {i} in the database\",\n",
    "     \"generated_query\": f\"SELECT metric_{i} FROM analytics WHERE date = CURDATE()\"}\n",
    "    for i in range(50)\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"batch_progress\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    if HAS_TQDM:\n",
    "        pbar = tqdm(total=len(large_batch), desc=\"Warming cache\")\n",
    "        count = await medha.store_many(\n",
    "            large_batch,\n",
    "            on_progress=lambda done, total: pbar.update(done - pbar.n),\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        pbar.close()\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        def simple_progress(done: int, total: int) -> None:\n",
    "            print(f\"  Progress: {done}/{total}\", end=\"\\r\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        count = await medha.store_many(large_batch, on_progress=simple_progress)\n",
    "        print()\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"Stored {count} entries\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 3: TTL in Batch — `store_many(entries, ttl=86400)`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "daily_queries = [\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Today's active users\",   \"generated_query\": \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users WHERE DATE(last_seen) = CURDATE()\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Today's new signups\",    \"generated_query\": \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users WHERE DATE(created_at) = CURDATE()\"},\n",
    "    {\"question\": \"Today's revenue\",        \"generated_query\": \"SELECT SUM(amount) FROM orders WHERE DATE(created_at) = CURDATE()\"},\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"batch_ttl\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    count = await medha.store_many(daily_queries, ttl=86400)  # expire in 24 hours\n",
    "\n",
    "    results, _ = await medha._backend.scroll(\"batch_ttl\", limit=10)\n",
    "    print(f\"Stored {count} entries with ttl=86400\")\n",
    "    for r in results:\n",
    "        print(f\"  {r.original_question!r:35s}  expires_at={r.expires_at}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 4: `batch_embed_concurrency` — Parallel Embedding Chunks"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "settings_concurrent = Settings(\n",
    "    backend_type=\"memory\",\n",
    "    batch_embed_concurrency=3,   # embed 3 chunks concurrently\n",
    "    batch_size=10,               # each chunk = 10 entries\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"batch_embed_concurrency : {settings_concurrent.batch_embed_concurrency}\")\n",
    "print(f\"batch_size              : {settings_concurrent.batch_size}\")\n",
    "print(\"With 30 entries: 3 chunks × 10 entries, all embedded concurrently.\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Best for: cloud embedders (OpenAI, Cohere, Gemini) where network latency\")\n",
    "print(\"dominates — concurrency hides the round-trip time.\")\n",
    "print(\"For local FastEmbed: concurrency=1 is usually optimal (CPU-bound).")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 5: `warm_from_dataframe()` — Pandas Integration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build a DataFrame with custom column names\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame([\n",
    "    {\"nl_query\":    \"How many customers do we have?\",\n",
    "     \"sql_query\":   \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM customers\",\n",
    "     \"description\": \"Customer count\"},\n",
    "    {\"nl_query\":    \"Top 5 customers by spend\",\n",
    "     \"sql_query\":   \"SELECT customer_id, SUM(amount) FROM orders GROUP BY customer_id ORDER BY 2 DESC LIMIT 5\",\n",
    "     \"description\": \"Top spenders\"},\n",
    "    {\"nl_query\":    \"Customers without orders\",\n",
    "     \"sql_query\":   \"SELECT * FROM customers WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT customer_id FROM orders)\",\n",
    "     \"description\": \"Churned customers\"},\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"DataFrame shape: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(df[[\"nl_query\", \"sql_query\"]].to_string(index=False))\n",
    "print()\n",
    "\n",
    "async with Medha(\"from_df\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    count = await medha.warm_from_dataframe(\n",
    "        df,\n",
    "        question_col=\"nl_query\",\n",
    "        query_col=\"sql_query\",\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\"warm_from_dataframe() loaded {count} entries\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    hit = await medha.search(\"Total number of customers\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Search: strategy={hit.strategy.value}  query={hit.generated_query!r}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 6: `export_to_dataframe()` — Read All Entries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "async with Medha(\"export_demo\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    await medha.store_many(entries)  # reuse entries from Cell 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    df_export = await medha.export_to_dataframe()\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"Exported {len(df_export)} entries\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Columns: {list(df_export.columns)}\")\n",
    "    print()\n",
    "    print(df_export[[\"original_question\", \"generated_query\"]].head(5).to_string(index=False))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Save to CSV for offline analysis\n",
    "    df_export.to_csv(\"/tmp/medha_export.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "    print(\"\\nExported to /tmp/medha_export.csv\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 7: `dedup_collection()` — Remove Duplicate SQL"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "async with Medha(\"dedup_demo\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as medha:\n",
    "    # Store the same SQL via different question phrasings\n",
    "    await medha.store(\"Count all users\",             \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users\")\n",
    "    await medha.store(\"How many users are there?\",   \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users\")\n",
    "    await medha.store(\"Total registered users\",      \"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users\")\n",
    "    await medha.store(\"Active users list\",           \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE status = 'active'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    count_before = await medha._backend.count(\"dedup_demo\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Count before dedup : {count_before}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    removed = await medha.dedup_collection(strategy=\"keep_latest\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    count_after = await medha._backend.count(\"dedup_demo\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Removed {removed} duplicate(s)\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Count after dedup  : {count_after}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 8: Migration Pipeline — Export → Reimport with New Backend"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: Original cache (old backend / old embedder)\n",
    "print(\"Step 1 — Populate old cache\")\n",
    "async with Medha(\"old_cache\", embedder=embedder, settings=settings) as old_medha:\n",
    "    await old_medha.store_many(entries)\n",
    "    df_snapshot = await old_medha.export_to_dataframe()\n",
    "    print(f\"  Exported {len(df_snapshot)} entries\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 2: New cache (different collection name, same or new embedder)\n",
    "print(\"\\nStep 2 — Warm new cache from exported DataFrame\")\n",
    "new_settings = Settings(backend_type=\"memory\")  # or backend_type=\"qdrant\", lancedb, etc.\n",
    "async with Medha(\"new_cache\", embedder=embedder, settings=new_settings) as new_medha:\n",
    "    loaded = await new_medha.warm_from_dataframe(\n",
    "        df_snapshot,\n",
    "        question_col=\"original_question\",\n",
    "        query_col=\"generated_query\",\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    print(f\"  Loaded {loaded} entries into new cache\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    hit = await new_medha.search(\"Total user count\")\n",
    "    print(f\"  Search: strategy={hit.strategy.value}  query={hit.generated_query!r}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nMigration complete. Old cache can be retired.\")"
   ]
  }
